{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018a65BNCZN6UUgKZ6a5pnsu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WmVmHUbxF8hqPURaQnYZ1f","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack.md","content":"# Story 9-2: State schema migration for multi-stack\n\n## Status: backlog\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer upgrading codeharness,\nI want my existing state file to auto-migrate to the new multi-stack format,\nSo that I don't have to re-initialize.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC1: Given an old state file with `stack: 'nodejs'` and no `stacks` field, when `readState()` is called, then `state.stacks` is `['nodejs']` and `state.stack` is `'nodejs'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC2: Given a new state file with `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']`, when `readState()` is called, then `state.stacks` is `['nodejs', 'rust']` and `state.stack` is `'nodejs'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC3: Given a state file with neither `stack` nor `stacks`, when `readState()` is called, then `state.stacks` is `[]` and `state.stack` is `null` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC4: Given state is written via `writeState()` with `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']`, when the file is inspected, then it contains both `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']` AND `stack: 'nodejs'` for backward compat <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC5: Given `getDefaultState()` is called with a stack argument, then the returned state has both `stack` and `stacks` fields populated consistently <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC6: Given a corrupted state file triggers `recoverCorruptedState()`, then the recovered state has both `stack` and `stacks` fields populated from `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC7: Given `isValidState()` validates state, then it accepts both old-format (only `stack`) and new-format (both `stack` and `stacks`) state files <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC8: Given the full test suite runs after all changes, then all existing single-stack tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Technical Notes\n\n### HarnessState Interface Changes\n\nFile: `src/lib/state.ts` — `HarnessState` interface.\n\nAdd a new `stacks` field:\n\n```ts\nexport interface HarnessState {\n  harness_version: string;\n  initialized: boolean;\n  stack: string | null;          // kept for backward compat — always first of stacks, or null\n  stacks: StackName[];           // NEW — all detected stacks\n  app_type?: 'server' | 'cli' | 'web' | 'agent' | 'generic';\n  // ... rest unchanged\n}\n```\n\nImport `StackName` from `./stack-detect.js`.\n\n### Migration Logic in `readState()`\n\nAfter parsing the YAML frontmatter, add a migration step:\n\n```ts\nfunction migrateState(state: HarnessState): HarnessState {\n  // Old format: has stack but no stacks\n  if (state.stack && !state.stacks) {\n    state.stacks = [state.stack as StackName];\n  }\n  // New format: has stacks but derive stack for compat\n  if (state.stacks && state.stacks.length > 0 && !state.stack) {\n    state.stack = state.stacks[0];\n  }\n  // Neither present\n  if (!state.stacks) {\n    state.stacks = [];\n  }\n  if (!state.stack && (!state.stacks || state.stacks.length === 0)) {\n    state.stack = null;\n    state.stacks = [];\n  }\n  // Ensure stack is always first of stacks\n  if (state.stacks && state.stacks.length > 0) {\n    state.stack = state.stacks[0];\n  }\n  return state;\n}\n```\n\nApply `migrateState()` after `parse()` in both `readState()` and `readStateWithBody()`.\n\n### writeState() Dual-Write\n\n`writeState()` must ensure both `stack` and `stacks` are persisted. Before serialization:\n\n```ts\nif (state.stacks && state.stacks.length > 0) {\n  state.stack = state.stacks[0];\n}\n```\n\nThis ensures old consumers reading `stack` still work.\n\n### getDefaultState() Update\n\n```ts\nexport function getDefaultState(stack?: string | null): HarnessState {\n  return {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    stack: stack ?? null,\n    stacks: stack ? [stack as StackName] : [],\n    // ...\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### isValidState() Update\n\nThe validator must accept both old-format and new-format state:\n- Old format: `stack` present, no `stacks` — valid (migration will add stacks)\n- New format: both `stack` and `stacks` present — valid\n- `stacks` must be an array if present\n\n### recoverCorruptedState() Update\n\nUse both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()`:\n\n```ts\nfunction recoverCorruptedState(dir: string): HarnessState {\n  warn('State file corrupted — recreating from detected config');\n  const stack = detectStack(dir);\n  const allStacks = detectStacks(dir);\n  const state = getDefaultState(stack);\n  state.stacks = allStacks.map(s => s.stack);\n  writeState(state, dir);\n  return state;\n}\n```\n\nNote: `detectStack()` returns root-only stack (per 9-1 code review fix), while `detectStacks()` returns all stacks. The `stacks` field should contain all unique stack names (deduped).\n\n### Import Required\n\nAdd to `src/lib/state.ts`:\n```ts\nimport { detectStack, detectStacks, type StackName } from './stack-detect.js';\n```\n\nThe existing import of `detectStack` is already present. Add `detectStacks` and `StackName`.\n\n### Breaking Change Risk\n\nNone. All additions are backward-compatible:\n- `stacks` is a new optional-at-read field (migration fills it in)\n- `stack` is preserved for all existing consumers\n- Old state files auto-migrate on first read\n\n## Files to Change\n\n- `src/lib/state.ts` — Add `stacks: StackName[]` to `HarnessState`, add `migrateState()` function, update `readState()` and `readStateWithBody()` to call migration, update `writeState()` to dual-write, update `getDefaultState()` to populate `stacks`, update `isValidState()` to accept old and new formats, update `recoverCorruptedState()` to use `detectStacks()`\n- `src/lib/__tests__/state.test.ts` — Add migration tests: old→new format, new format round-trip, neither-field case, dual-write verification, `getDefaultState` stacks field, recovery with stacks, `isValidState` acceptance of both formats\n\n## Tasks/Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Import `detectStacks` and `StackName` from `./stack-detect.js` in `state.ts`\n- [ ] Task 2: Add `stacks: StackName[]` field to `HarnessState` interface\n- [ ] Task 3: Implement `migrateState()` function that normalizes old/new/empty state formats\n- [ ] Task 4: Apply `migrateState()` in `readState()` after YAML parse and validation\n- [ ] Task 5: Apply `migrateState()` in `readStateWithBody()` after YAML parse and validation\n- [ ] Task 6: Update `writeState()` to ensure `stack` is always synced from `stacks[0]` before serialization\n- [ ] Task 7: Update `getDefaultState()` to include `stacks` field\n- [ ] Task 8: Update `isValidState()` to accept old-format state (no `stacks`) as valid\n- [ ] Task 9: Update `recoverCorruptedState()` to populate `stacks` from `detectStacks()`\n- [ ] Task 10: Add test — old format migration (`stack: 'nodejs'`, no `stacks`) → `stacks: ['nodejs']`\n- [ ] Task 11: Add test — new format read (`stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']`) → `stack: 'nodejs'`\n- [ ] Task 12: Add test — neither field present → `stacks: []`, `stack: null`\n- [ ] Task 13: Add test — `writeState()` dual-write verification (both fields in YAML output)\n- [ ] Task 14: Add test — `getDefaultState()` returns consistent `stack` and `stacks`\n- [ ] Task 15: Add test — `isValidState()` accepts old-format and new-format\n- [ ] Task 16: Add test — round-trip: write multi-stack state → read → verify both fields\n- [ ] Task 17: Run full test suite — verify zero regressions\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n(to be filled during implementation)\n\n## File List\n\n(to be filled during implementation)\n\n## Change Log\n\n(to be filled during implementation)\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":546,"cache_read_input_tokens":33935,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":546,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01EPZD8GcmYWyL2DU72ZXXeA","session_id":"90f5ac9b-34a6-4398-bbd9-dd5bc4930bef","uuid":"6ab20df3-52f8-44ef-9baf-eb81a552bffc"}
