{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S3z5HDAFArZjH9jd81j8Qm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 7)\n     2→\n     3→### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — create-story (2026-03-23T14:24Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Ambiguity:** Epic says `stacks: string[]` but `StackName` union type exists from story 9-1. Chose `StackName[]` for type safety.\n     6→- **Missing context:** `InitResult` in `types.ts` may need `stacks` field but epic FR4 doesn't explicitly call it out — implied by scope.\n     7→- **Risk:** `detectStacks()` can return duplicate stack names from multiple directories. `stacks` field needs deduplication.\n     8→- **Observation:** All 8 ACs are cli-verifiable via unit tests — no external dependencies.\n     9→\n    10→### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:32Z)\n    11→\n    12→- **Pre-existing type errors:** `bridge.test.ts` implicit `any`, `run.test.ts` spread arg type error, `stack.test.ts` missing `endpoint`, `status.test.ts` missing `timeoutSummary`. None from this story.\n    13→- **Workaround:** Used `stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]` instead of `as const` in `stack.test.ts` because readonly tuples aren't assignable to `StackName[]`.\n    14→- **Risk:** `recoverCorruptedState()` recovery path not directly unit-tested for `stacks` field — would need planted `package.json` in temp dir.\n    15→- **Observation:** 19 new tests added, all 3098 tests pass with 0 failures.\n    16→\n    17→### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — code-review (2026-03-23T14:36Z)\n    18→\n    19→- **HIGH (fixed):** `init-project.ts` never persisted multi-stacks to state file — only single root stack written. All `detectStacks()` results lost on init.\n    20→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `writeState()` mutated caller's state object via `state.stack = state.stacks[0]` side effect.\n    21→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `isValidState()` accepted `stacks: [42, true]` as valid — no element type checking.\n    22→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` produced inconsistent `stack: null` / `stacks: ['nodejs']` state.\n    23→- **LOW (not fixed):** `migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName` without validating against known stack names.\n    24→- **LOW (not fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()` — detection runs twice.\n    25→- **LOW (not fixed):** Flaky test in `sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts > writeStateAtomic` — shared file race condition under parallel execution.\n    26→- **Coverage gap:** `init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field after init. No test for recovery when root null but subdirs have stacks.\n    27→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90f5ac9b-34a6-4398-bbd9-dd5bc4930bef","uuid":"e174993c-a598-43e7-abd0-4de11aa7dcfd","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:45:59.881Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 7)\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — create-story (2026-03-23T14:24Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** Epic says `stacks: string[]` but `StackName` union type exists from story 9-1. Chose `StackName[]` for type safety.\n- **Missing context:** `InitResult` in `types.ts` may need `stacks` field but epic FR4 doesn't explicitly call it out — implied by scope.\n- **Risk:** `detectStacks()` can return duplicate stack names from multiple directories. `stacks` field needs deduplication.\n- **Observation:** All 8 ACs are cli-verifiable via unit tests — no external dependencies.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:32Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing type errors:** `bridge.test.ts` implicit `any`, `run.test.ts` spread arg type error, `stack.test.ts` missing `endpoint`, `status.test.ts` missing `timeoutSummary`. None from this story.\n- **Workaround:** Used `stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]` instead of `as const` in `stack.test.ts` because readonly tuples aren't assignable to `StackName[]`.\n- **Risk:** `recoverCorruptedState()` recovery path not directly unit-tested for `stacks` field — would need planted `package.json` in temp dir.\n- **Observation:** 19 new tests added, all 3098 tests pass with 0 failures.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — code-review (2026-03-23T14:36Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** `init-project.ts` never persisted multi-stacks to state file — only single root stack written. All `detectStacks()` results lost on init.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `writeState()` mutated caller's state object via `state.stack = state.stacks[0]` side effect.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `isValidState()` accepted `stacks: [42, true]` as valid — no element type checking.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` produced inconsistent `stack: null` / `stacks: ['nodejs']` state.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName` without validating against known stack names.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()` — detection runs twice.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Flaky test in `sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts > writeStateAtomic` — shared file race condition under parallel execution.\n- **Coverage gap:** `init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field after init. No test for recovery when root null but subdirs have stacks.\n","numLines":27,"startLine":1,"totalLines":27}}}
